{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b4b088a2-137d-466d-aa9b-b1325bd557e4","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API style (default in .NET 6+)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer or cookie auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` or use ASP.NET Core Identity. Run `dotnet new webapi --help` to see all available options for your SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0c49eca1-d113-4b2e-aa91-d65169fa0368","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context mentions dotnet). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":333,"requestId":"33C5:23056D:1F91A9A:235CCC5:69E819FD"},"id":"94881ed0-ef0b-4d65-acec-2c76e3ac6bdc","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:44:52.682Z","parentId":"64ce98fa-5ad4-4224-9fba-e9da915bc0dd"}
